by Synne Industries » Sun Jun 06, 2021 8:48 am

The Dominion of Chaos wrote:*insert obligatory logbooks that go from ‘Everything is fine’ to ‘Ah, everything is not fine’; or ‘Serve the hivemind’ or something*


I mean I see why people do it, it's easy. Hell, I don't remember anything specific but I probably did it as part of my early Initiative work. It shoves what it's trying to say right in the reader's face and as I said before, it's easy and at first, it works. It stops working once you see the same damn thing a dozen times. Now personally I feel like the issue here is pacing. In a very generalized example of the "haha look at the dimensional horror beyond your comprehension despite the fact that you're comprehending it right now" logbook, everything just feels so immediate and disconnected though this might have more to do about the base concept rather than the writing conveying that concept. It, whatever that might be is usually an eldritch monstrosity, some big scary dimension, or something else that an audience is supposed to be immediately terrified of. This, I personally do not like. I don't like it because it throws a lot of the writing leading up to it in the trash, someone could scroll down to the bottom of the factbook and just say "oh, that's what they were trying to do". Very rarely on NS do you see fridge horror done right. That sinking realization at the end of a good series of dispatches or whatnot that all those little things that you once thought were insignificant add-up to something truly terrifying in the context of the writing is something I wish to see done.

Hell if I know where I was going with this mini-rant. td;dr, make your writing mean something.

There’s so much to do with characters that possess actual character with positive and negative traits.

by Netherlands Australia » Sun Jun 06, 2021 2:12 pm

I have a big problem with nations being unable to carry their historical weight. If you're going to be Nazi Germany, be Nazi Germany, but for 5h3 love of God make it make sense. If you just say "Nazis but not Nazis!!!" It just seems half-assed. Make it make sense: a coup, or anything! And the same goes for the USSR, or any country with a bloody and controversial history: you gotta take it in your stride, instead of just tossing aside pretty much decades of history because you don't like it. Build up from the bottom if you want, but damnit if you want to have an alt-history Germany where they won the war, you need to acknowledge that they did some messed up stuff afterwards, or how the USSR put people into work camps because they didn't clap hard enough, or oppression of natives in post-colonial states, or ANYTHING to make it that little bit more realistic.

South Americanastan wrote:
Cavirfi wrote:What's a summerposter? I am hearing people use the term lately.

I've never heard that specific term before but I think it's referring to NS Summer.


Summerposters are the people who can't be super active during the school year because... school. So they come on during summer break when they have time off to play NS. They're inexperienced, but that does not necessarily correlate to how long they've been on the site. I've seen summerposters who've been on this site for years (albeit probably while under 13 against NS's TOS. most of them are like 13 or 14) and they still haven't learned anything. Generally they make shitty, one line replies to other players in F7 games and try to jump into every military RP or make 800 RP threads themselves. They constantly interject themselves where they are not wanted. Some people have sympathy for them because they're "just trying to learn the game" but the problem is that most of them will throw their shitty work across the site for many years before they either get DOSed or mature and realize that they've really not done a very good job and try to improve somewhat. The former happens much, much more often.
Currently in the process of revamping all of my lore, including my signature. It's gonna probably take a while, better make yourself comfortable.

I've seen summerposters who've been on this site for years (albeit probably while under 13 against NS's TOS. most of them are like 13 or 14) and they still haven't learned anything. Generally they make shitty, one line replies to other players in F7 games and try to jump into every military RP or make 800 RP threads themselves. They constantly interject themselves where they are not wanted. Some people have sympathy for them because they're "just trying to learn the game" but the problem is that most of them will throw their shitty work across the site for many years before they either get DOSed or mature and realize that they've really not done a very good job and try to improve somewhat. The former happens much, much more often.

I know what they are, I've just never heard the specific term "Summerposters" to refer to them.
